<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-131-696  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 131 696.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  March 20 1989 v6 n11 p27(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>System simplifies data retrieval for Oracle users. (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Dynamics Research Corp. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    DRCO.andO;Product:   Spock (Computer program)Oracle (Data base management system) (computer programs).andO;Topic:     Natural Language InterfacesData BasesQuery LanguagesReport GeneratorsSoftware PackagesProduct IntroductionEnhancements.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>System Simplifies Data Retrieval For Oracle UsersandM;ANDOVER, Mass.andP;  -- The systems division of Dynamics Research has announced anew version of Spock, the company's natural-language database query andreporting system.andP;  Officials also announced that in addition to currentproduct support of Oracle's database, Spock is scheduled to become availablefor Ingres, Sybase and Rdb later this year.andM;&quot;The new version offers a data dictionary builder, which automatically buildsthe basic knowledge base of the database so that Spock knows what's outthere,&quot; said John Ragosta, the company's accounts executive.andP;  &quot;It also hassimple start-up and easy maintenance in case you want to change a table orattribute a value.&quot;andM;Spock translates English requests into an internal global language thatallows the request to be routed automatically to the appropriate database.andO;Spock's Data Dictionary determines the routing, company officials said.andM;Requests reach individual databases in the base's own language.andP;  Officialssaid Spock can transfer data quickly because a data accessor is attached toeach database management system, and Spock is not restricted to passing datathrough a central hub as is the case with most &quot;star&quot; systems.andM;Improvements to version 2.1 of Spock include the Data Dictionary, which readsOracle tables to build the initial database so that new users can begin usingSpock immediately without having to wait for customization.andP;  Otherenhancements include simpler screen displays; faster data access; improvederror checking; and increased capacity, allowing users to access 300 tablesper database.andM;&quot;This version [with the Data Dictionary] offers immediate access to strategicinformation,&quot; he added.andP;  &quot;There's nothing more frustrating for the end userthan to have to wait three to four days for someone else to deliverinformation.andP;  [Corporations might ask] 'What's it worth to us to be able togo over to the workstation, type in a request, and see the information?'andO;With Oracle, they have to be trained in Sequel.&quot;andM;Spock 2.1 is available now for Oracle, and the price for a one-userworkstation license is $3,500, with options for volume discounts.andM;Dynamics Research Corp. is located at 60 Frontage Road, Andover, MA 01810,(508) 475-9090.andO;</TEXT></DOC>